## TF-IDF

**IDF (Inverse Document Frequency)** is a statistical measure used in information retrieval to quantify how **important** or **rare** a word is across a collection of documents (corpus).

---

### üîπ Why IDF?

* Some words (like "the", "is", "and") appear in nearly every document ‚Äî they don‚Äôt help distinguish one document from another.  
* **IDF downweights common words** and boosts rare, more informative ones.

---

### üîπ IDF Formula:

[![][image1]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%20%5Ctext%7BIDF%7D\(t\)%20%3D%20%5Clog%5Cleft\(%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7B1%20%2B%20%5Ctext%7BDF%7D\(t\)%7D%5Cright\)%20#0)

Where:

* [![][image2]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=t#0): the term (word)  
* [![][image3]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=N#0): total number of documents  
* [![][image4]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=DF\(t\)#0): number of documents that contain term t  
* [![][image5]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=1%20%2B#0) in the denominator is for smoothing to avoid division by zero.

---

### üî∏ Example:

Assume you have 1000 documents:

* Word "the" appears in **950 documents** ‚Üí  
    
  [![][image6]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%20%5Ctext%7BIDF\(the\)%7D%20%3D%20%5Clog%5Cleft\(%5Cfrac%7B1000%7D%7B951%7D%5Cright\)%20%5Capprox%200.02%20#0)  
    
  ‚ûù Very low weight  
    
* Word "photosynthesis" appears in **10 documents** ‚Üí  
    
  [![][image7]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%20%5Ctext%7BIDF\(photosynthesis\)%7D%20%3D%20%5Clog%5Cleft\(%5Cfrac%7B1000%7D%7B11%7D%5Cright\)%20%5Capprox%202.0%20#0)  
    
  ‚ûù High weight

---

### üîπ IDF is used in:

* **TF-IDF** \= Term Frequency √ó Inverse Document Frequency ‚ûù Emphasizes terms that are frequent **in one document** but **rare overall**.  

---

Here‚Äôs a **side-by-side table** illustrating **TF (Term Frequency)**, **IDF (Inverse Document Frequency)**, and **TF-IDF** effects for different words in a collection of **1000 documents**.

---

### **Example Table of TF, IDF, and TF-IDF**

| Word | TF in Document (Count) | DF (Docs Containing Word) | IDF [![][image8]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7B1%2BDF%7D\)#0) | TF-IDF [![][image9]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=TF%20%5Ctimes%20IDF#0) |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **the** | 20 | 950 | [![][image10]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(1000%2F951\)%20%5Capprox%200.02#0) | **0.4** |
| **is** | 10 | 900 | [![][image11]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(1000%2F901\)%20%5Capprox%200.05#0) | **0.5** |
| **apple** | 5 | 100 | [![][image12]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(1000%2F101\)%20%5Capprox%201.0#0) | **5.0** |
| **photosynthesis** | 3 | 10 | [![][image13]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(1000%2F11\)%20%5Capprox%202.0#0) | **6.0** |
| **quantum** | 2 | 5 | [![][image14]](https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=%5Clog\(1000%2F6\)%20%5Capprox%202.5#0) | **5.0** |

---

### **Key Observations:**

1. **Common words ("the", "is") have low IDF** ‚Üí Since they appear in almost all documents, their IDF is **close to 0**, meaning they contribute **little to TF-IDF**.  
2. **Less frequent words ("photosynthesis", "quantum") have high IDF** ‚Üí Since they appear in **fewer documents**, they are more **important** in distinguishing documents.  
3. **TF-IDF balances term frequency and importance** ‚Üí Even if a term appears multiple times in a document (high TF), it **only gets a high TF-IDF if it is rare in the corpus**.
